dct_title_s: A general map of the River Sanaga or Senegal from the Falls of Govina to the Ocean; taken by a French engineer in 1718, & drawn by the Sr. d'Anville, from ye particular draughts publish'd by Labat
dct_description_sm: "Plate 186, No. 106, Vol. 2, p. 400" in lower left corner.
The French founded St Louis at the mouth of the Senegal River in 1659 and a trading post up-river at Fort St Joseph.
